		<title>Failure of Success Criterion 1.4.13 due to providing no mechanism to dismiss content on hover or focus without moving focus</title>
		<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="https://rawgit.com/w3c/wcag21/master/css/sources.css"/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<h1>Failure of Success Criterion 1.4.13 due to providing no mechanism to dismiss content on hover or focus without moving focus</h1>
		<section id="meta">
			<h2>Metadata</h2>
			<p id="id"></p>
			<p id="technology">general</p>
			<p id="type">sufficient</p>
		</section>
		<section id="applicability">
			<h2>When to Use</h2>
			<h3>Applicability</h3>
			<p>The Technique us applicable to any technology that supports the display of additional content on pointer hover or keyboard focus.</p>
		</section>
		<section id="description">
			<h2>Description</h2>
			<p>The objective of this failure is to describe a situation where users find it impossible to dismiss content appearing on top of a page when hovering over particular elements or keyboard-focusing these elements, without moving the pointer or the keyboard focus.</p>
		</section>
		<section id="examples">
			<h2>Examples</h2>
<ul>
	<li>When moving the pointer over a link or when keyboard-focussing that link, a page displays a pop-up that obscures content. The pop-up stays open. A close-button im the popup can only be activated using pointer input. The pop-up stays open when tabbing on, obstructing the visibility of content on the page. Closing the pop-up via the ESC key or some other documented keyboard command is not implemented.</li>
    <li>When moving the pointer over a link or when keyboard-focussing that link, a page displays a pop-up that obscures content. The pop-up closes automatically when moving the pointer or tabbing to the next focusable element, but cannot be dismissed while the pointer or keyboard focus stays on the trigger that opened the close-up, for example, by avtivating the trigger or by using a keyboard command like ESC.</li>
	</ul>
		</section>
		<section id="resources">
		<h2>Resources<</h2>
			
		</section>
		<section id="tests">
			<h2>Tests</h2>
			<section class="test-procedure">
				<h3>Procedure</h3>
				<ol>
					<li>Determine if content appears when moving hover or keyboard focus onto triggering elements of the page, such as links or buttons. If this is the case:</li>
    <li>Check if activating the trigger dismisses the content</li>
    <li>Check if the ESC key dismisses the content.</li>
    <li>Check if any other documented keyboard shortcut dismisses the content.</li>
				</ol>
			</section>
			<section class="test-results">
				<h3>Expected Results</h3>
				<ul>
					<li>If #1 is true, one option of #2, #3, #4 is true</li>
				</ul>
			</section>
		</section>
